reviewText: To relocate the lighthouse some 180 feet from its original location may have cost the Indian tribe some three million dollar plus but they certainly had the blessing of the mother nature, ten tons of steel, 800 blocks of wood as well as the help of one of the top world's most knowledgeable, elite and humorous moving contractor. If you are a mariner or have any passion for engineering, construction and history then this is a must see video for you. Bravo.
